File: Members of National University of Science and Technology (NUST) work on specimens in a COVID-19 laboratory testing centre, at Mpilo Hospital in Bulawayo, Zimbabwe. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa has 276,242 confirmed COVID-19 cases. President Cyril Ramaphosa made the announcement during a media briefing on Sunday. READ: Gauteng becomes COVID-19 epicentre Ramaphosa says the Covid-19 storm is upon us. He says infections and deaths continue to spike each day. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.